Commentary: this is simply brilliant at wide long-on. Liton Das, running across from deep midwicket, had to be aware of the long-on fielder running across fill tilt, so he not only had to move away from his line to prevent a collision but also at the same time have his eyes on the ball. It can be distracting at the best of times but he somehow managed to keep his composure and pull off a stunner. Coming to the ball, it was nicely tossed up, dipped on Brathwaite but he went through with the shot. And because he didn't get to the pitch of it, there wasn't the kind of power he would've liked.
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Brathwaite, OUT
